fields.Title: WHIRLING F2 ORB / Ultraliberal Quest Initiation
fields.Description: Savoir Faire tells you it's time to stop playing the market and make some real cash so you can fulfil your heart's desire.

Savoir Faire: "*One* coin. The first of many. Imag..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *One* coin. The first of many. Imagine so many coins you're going to need to hire someone to help you manage all your wealth.

fields.Dialogue Text: By all accounts this place should be *swarming* with artist-types. It's just a matter of time until you meet one. Look for squats and cheap rentals, we might even chance upon a *political artivist* here.

fields.Dialogue Text: What's up? I'm worried about what's *down*, broke boy. I'm talking about your severe lack of money.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "No, you don't! You just keep mutter..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, you don't! You just keep muttering about your 'economic self-interest' and not doing anything about it. Yeah, I heard you back there. What the hell was that?!

fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, win *whom* back?

fields.Dialogue Text: What? No, screw that shit-show. You're at the centre of this one. Come on down, contestant, you're about to make some *money*.

fields.Dialogue Text: Stop grumbling, it's time to move. Are you in or are you out?

fields.Dialogue Text: Oh, so now it's Savvy? What's up, buddy?

fields.Dialogue Text: Take heed of these wise words. *You're* in charge. 'Sorry' is a beggar's plea reserved for those beneath you.

fields.Title: You: "Do I know you?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Do I know you?

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Oh, it can. But first you need to *..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh, it can. But first you need to *enter* the market. Right now you're as good as Samir Loisir eating dirt in Gurdi's immense network of mines.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Samir Loisir was a Gurdi businessma..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Samir Loisir was a Gurdi businessman who made his first millions selling kilograms of the ultra-rare mineral phasium to luxury jeweller ZachaÃ«l et Cie. He made the rest of his many millions through wise investments and the invention of pleochroic lights.

fields.Dialogue Text: Perfect, all you have to do is *pretend* to have taste. This will be your weapon when swindling artists for their overpriced 'work'.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Once we've brought in the millions..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Once we've brought in the millions you can be a tree log for all I care, but first we've got to work on increasing your net worth.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Exactly. Not making money when you'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Exactly. Not making money when you're asleep, are you? If you wanna be rich you better work until your fingers bleed. You can sleep when you die.

fields.Dialogue Text: Just take my money and leave me alone!

fields.Dialogue Text: Hey, money-mouth. Eendracht. The impeccable hustler-provider of the seventh generation. It's showtime with Savvy!

fields.Dialogue Text: But Savvy's got your back. Savvy's going to book you a charter flight with eighty birds of prey on board, to a land where the streets are paved with krugerrands and fixed-income securities. You'll try again, but this time with *money*. You'll win her back.

fields.Title: You: "I was asleep."
fields.Dialogue Text: I was asleep.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "That's right! It's time to stop mut..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's right! It's time to stop muttering about your 'economic self-interest' and actually do something about it. Yeah, I heard you back there. What the hell was that?!

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "What is this, the turn of the centu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What is this, the turn of the century? The world's moved beyond paintings. You want something *experimental* -- intramuscular puppetry, hyperrealistic vapour-porn, meditation opera...

fields.Dialogue Text: Good, good, gotta spread the gospel. But talk alone doesn't bring in the cash. It's time for step two.

fields.Dialogue Text: What do you expect? I'm an ultraliberal. I speak ultraliberal-ese.

fields.Dialogue Text: (Your pecs dance.) No more sleep it is. A frazzled ride through eternity without pause. Hissing pistons pushed to the extreme.

fields.Dialogue Text: Are you in?

fields.Dialogue Text: Cuno? Cuno is an artist.

fields.Dialogue Text: Yeah, swindle-father. Papa-preneur. Look, this is serious. No time for distractions. It's time to make *money*. Lots of it.

fields.Title: You: "I'm just tired of being a low-net-w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'm just tired of being a low-net-worth-individual. It must be *the curse*.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Did Ilona Wihuri-Vilakone blame gho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Did Ilona Wihuri-Vilakone blame ghosts? How about Admiral Gustav Lestock? Samir Loisir grew up in the coal mines of Gurdi eating dirt, and he still managed to make FIFTY-FIVE BILLION REÃL in his lifetime. So stop with the excuses.

fields.Dialogue Text: Do you see any stock markets in Martinaise? No? That's because for those living in the outskirts, the market is *nothing*. Just ghost numbers flicking through time. A spectral sport they're not invited to play.
